com.navis.framework.portal.extensions

Interface IMobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext

    public interface IMobileTwoFieldSortDomainQueryContext
    TODO is this not more generic than just N4Mobile? This object encapsulates the information necessary for performing a two field sort of a domain query on a mobile program. The information encapsulated is. - The first field to sort (MetafieldId). This includes two metafields; the mobile metafield that is defined in the mobile variform and the metafield on the backing entity. It is possible that the entity field is null in which case the domain query is not modified (sorting occurs in code). - The second field to sort (MetafieldId). This includes two metafields; the mobile metafield that is defined in the mobile variform and the metafield on the backing entity. It is possible that the entity field is null in which case the domain query is not modified (sorting occurs in code). - The sort direction of the first field (ascending / descending). - The sort direction of the second field (ascending / descending). This object also contains additional fields that will be added to the domain query before it is executed, and will also contain the domain query after it has been executed. This is passed through the Finder API (e.g., UnitFinder) when building a result list for a query so the query can be enhanced by the caller, and so the query is available to the caller. As is, the finder returns the result and not the query. This is available in the handler for the code extension whose type is MOBILE_QUERY_RESULT_PROVIDER. The state of this is updated each time the user clicks on a column header in the mobile table.
    Author:
    Amos Parlante

    • Method Detail

      • onChangeFieldsBeingSorted

        void onChangeFieldsBeingSorted(MetafieldId inMobileFieldSorted,
                               boolean inSortInAscendingOrder)
        This method is used to change the columns being sorted. It is called by the mobile framework when the user clicks on an additional column. The default implementation makes the current primary column being sorted the secondary column and makes the passed in column the primary column.
        Parameters:
        inMobileFieldSorted - The MetafieldId backing the mobile field (usually column in a table) being sorted.
        inSortInAscendingOrder - The new sort order for the primary column.

      • getVariformId

        java.lang.String getVariformId()
        This returns the variform Id of the table being sorted.
        Returns:
        Returns the variform ID of the mobile table being sorted.

      • getMobileFirstSortField

        @Nullable
MetafieldId getMobileFirstSortField()
        This returns the MetafieldId (mobile metafieldId) for the first column being sorted. If this field is null then there is no sorting.
        Returns:
        The first field to sort against.

      • getEntityFirstSortField

        @Nullable
MetafieldId getEntityFirstSortField()
        This returns the MetafieldId on the entity that is being sorted for the first column. This can be applied to the DomainQuery with a sort clause. This can return null, in which case the DomainQuery is not modified.
        Returns:
        The first field to sort against.

      • isFirstSortAscendingOrder

        boolean isFirstSortAscendingOrder()
        This is used to determine the sort order of the first field being sorted. It returns true if the first column is being sorted in ascending order, otherwise, false is returned.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the first column is being sorted in ascending order.

      • getMobileSecondSortField

        @Nullable
MetafieldId getMobileSecondSortField()
        This returns the metafield Id (mobile metafieldId) for the second column being sorted. If this field is null then no second field is beign sorted.
        Returns:
        The second column to sort.

      • getEntitySecondSortField

        @Nullable
MetafieldId getEntitySecondSortField()
        This returns the MetafieldId on the entity that is being sorted for the second field. This will be applied to the DomainQuery with a sort clause. This can return null, in which case the DomainQuery is not modified.
        Returns:
        The first field to sort against.

      • isSecondSortAscendingOrder

        boolean isSecondSortAscendingOrder()
        This is used to determine the sort order of the second field being sorted. It returns true if the first column is being sorted in ascending order, otherwise, false is returned.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the first column is being sorted in ascending order.

      • getAdditionalFieldsToRetrieve

        @NotNull
java.util.List<MetafieldId> getAdditionalFieldsToRetrieve()
        This returns a list of additional fields that will be added to the query and retrieved. It is assumed the caller of this method understands the context of the query and the fields being added belong to the entity. No error checking is performed.
        Returns:
        A list of additional fields that will be retrieved on the entity.

      • setDomainQueryResultLastExecuted

        void setDomainQueryResultLastExecuted(@Nullable
                                      QueryResult inDomainQuery)
        This method is used to set the domain query that was last executed using this context. This is set after the domain query is executed for downstream processing of the query.
        Parameters:
        inDomainQuery - The domain query that was just executed.

      • getDomainQueryResultLastExecuted

        @Nullable
QueryResult getDomainQueryResultLastExecuted()
        This method returns the last domain query that was configured by this context. This method can return null when no domain query has been executed against this contxt yet. This is not a generic method that Carina can handle so product code will need to be done for the various mobile programs if this pattern is needed. It was added to the mobile reefer so that can be used as an example.
        Returns:
        The last domain query executed that was configured by this context.
